  "school": "ICT",
  "asset": "USOIL",
  "timeframe": "5M",
  "market_context": "USOIL is trading down into an hourly bullish fair value gap. On the 5-minute chart, price taps the HTF FVG with an initial small sweep, then produces a lower-timeframe sweep of a swing low before forming a series of down-close candles that get closed through.",
  "key_observation": "Because the series of down-close candles forming the order block is large, entering at the opening price gives only 1.3R to the failure-swing highs. Using the mean threshold (50% of the OB body range) as the entry nearly doubles the risk-to-reward to 2.6R.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the higher timeframe context — price reaching into an hourly bullish fair value gap, establishing an important level.",
    "Step 2: Wait for a liquidity sweep on the 5-minute; note the first small sweep is not clean and prefer a defined swing low to be swept.",
    "Step 3: Observe a second, lower-timeframe sweep that takes out a clearer swing low.",
    "Step 4: Identify the series of down-close candles before the change in state of delivery and wait for price to close over them, validating the order block.",
    "Step 5: Mark target as the failure-swing highs above; note that using the OB opening price as entry with stop on the low gives only 1.3R.",
    "Step 6: Apply a 0.5 Fib from body low to body high of the OB to plot the mean threshold and use that as the entry instead.",
    "Step 7: Confirm the new risk-to-reward improves to approximately 2.6R with stop unchanged on the low.",
    "Step 8: Manage the trade — though it takes time, price eventually reaches the failure-swing highs, hitting the target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached the failure-swing high target; mean threshold entry delivered approximately 2.6R versus 1.3R from the opening-price entry.",
  "lessons": "When an order block consists of a large series of down-close candles, entering at the opening price often makes risk-to-reward unattractive. Switching to the mean threshold (50% of OB body) preserves OB validity while materially improving R:R.",
